result.execSummary:
The defendant Navarro Nelson II was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Theft-Movable Property <=$2500 [Modifiers: Penalties for Misdemeanors-Class "A"], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.20(1)(a).
  • Criminal Damage to Property [Modifiers: Penalties for Misdemeanors-Class "A"], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.01(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Navarro Nelson in court with attorney Matthew Adrian Lamke.  Defendant Navarro Nelson in custody.  Owen M. Piotrowski appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Sentencing proceeded. Statements by parties, Sonjai M., and defendant. 

AS TO COUNT 1 AMENDED
Court ordered defendant to serve 6 MONTHS in the House of Correction, which can be served in the Wisconsin State Prison System, consecutive to count 2 and count 1 in 15CF3228. Court STAYED sentence and placed defendant on PROBATION for 24 MONTHS.

AS TO COUNT 2
Court ordered defendant to serve 6 MONTHS in the House of Correction, which can be served in the Wisconsin State Prison System, consecutive to count 1 and count 1 in 15CF3228. Court STAYED sentence and placed defendant on PROBATION for 24 MONTHS.

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION
-Batterers Intervention program.
-Parenting classes.
-Mental health evaluation, take all prescribed medications.
-AODA assessment, comply with recommended treatment.
-Absolute sobriety.
-Treatment and/or counseling as determined by agent.
-No contact with victim Sonjai M. unless approved by the agent. Court grants third party contact for purpose of time with the child/children. Agent to approve third party.
-Obtain/maintain employment.
-Obtain GED/HSED.
-No contact with firearms.
-Pay all MANDATORY court costs, fees, and surcharges including: DNA surcharges to be paid during period of probation. Failure to pay results in a civil judgment.
-Court WAIVED all NON-Mandatory court costs, fees and surcharges due to inability to pay.
-Provide DNA Sample.
-Restitution set at ZERO.

*Court finds defendant is NOT eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program OR the Wisconsin Substance Abuse Program.
*Court advised defendant of right to seek post conviction relief.
*Court advised due to felony conviction the defendant is prohibited from firearm possession, and defendant's voting rights are suspended and may not vote until civil rights are restored.

Filed: Notice of Right to Seek Post-Conviction Relief and Memorandum of Conditions of Probation.

Probation Review Hearing in branch 24.  Probation Review Hearing scheduled for June 3, 2016 at 01:30 pm.

Parties have reached a resolution. 

AS TO COUNTS 1 AMENDED AND COUNT 2
Defendant changes plea(s) to GUILTY. Defendant examined as to plea, advised of Constitutional Rights and the maximum penalties. Court found that the defendant knowingly, voluntarily and intelligently waived rights.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights form, Addendum, and Jury Instructions received and filed. Parties stipulate to the Criminal Complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea(s).  Court found defendant GUILTY and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record.  

Court ordered defendant REMANDED into the custody of the Milwaukee County Sheriff's Department.

Case adjourned to branch 24 for Sentencing.

Defendant Navarro Nelson in court with attorney Matthew Adrian Lamke.  Defendant Navarro Nelson in custody.  Sarra Mae Kiaie appeared for the State of Wisconsin. CMC. Amended Information, received and filed.

Count 1: Theft (Value Not Exceeding $2,500.00), contrary to Wisconsin Statutes section(s) 943.20(1)(a) and (3)(a), and 939.51(3)(a), a Class A Misdemeanor. 
Count 2: Criminal Damage to Property (Less than $2,500.00 Damage), contrary to Wisconsin Statutes section(s) 943.01(1) and 939.51(3)(a), a Class A Misdemeanor.

Defendant Navarro Nelson in court with attorney Matthew Adrian Lamke.  Defendant Navarro Nelson in custody.  Sarra Mae Kiaie appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
Deputy Court Clerk: rmm.  
Doctor's report reviewed by the parties.  The court finds the defendant not competent to proceed but likely to become competent within the statutory time period.  if provided with appropriate treatment, is likely to become competent within 12 months or within the maximum sentence specified for the most serious offense, whichever is less.  The court orders the proceedings suspended and committed the defendant to the Department of Health Services for an indeterminate term not to exceed 12 months, or the maximum sentence specified for the most serious offense, whichever is less.    Defendant is found not competent to refuse medications or treatment for his mental condition as defined by sec. 971.17(3) and is hereby ordered to adhere to all medical and pharmacological treatment indicated by appropriate medical authorities.  Order of Commitment for Treatment (Incompetency) signed and filed.  Case adjourned to Branch 40.  Doctor's Report Return scheduled for December 22, 2015 at 01:30 pm.
